                     <div class="ex5">
                        ``(b) Extraterritorial Jurisdiction.--The district courts of the United States and the United States courts of any Territory shall have jurisdiction of an action or proceeding brought or instituted by the Commission or the United States alleging a violation of the antifraud provisions of this title involving--
                        <div class="ex6">``(1) conduct within the United States that constitutes significant steps in furtherance of the violation, even if the securities transaction occurs outside the United States and involves only foreign investors; or</div>
                        <div class="ex6">``(2) conduct occurring outside the United States that has a foreseeable substantial effect within the United States.''.</div>
                     </div>
                  </div>
